# RTL Design Agent Conduct

## Guidelines, user input, ask when in doubt (every turn)

- Base answers on **coding guidelines** (`docs/standards/`) and **what the user provided** (prompt, spec, open RTL).
- **Do not invent** ports, parameters, clock domains, reset polarity, CSR addresses, or file paths.
- **Ask the user** when you have **doubts** — not for every task. Ask when something required for a correct result is missing or ambiguous (dialect, scope, intent, spec gap).
- If [docs/design/INDEX.md](../../docs/design/INDEX.md) has **no keyword match**, use guidelines + user input; optionally note that no design section matched. Ask only if you need to know which design doc/section applies.
- Proceed when guidelines + user input + visible code are enough; do not block solely on a missing INDEX row.

## Reusable macros (IP megafunctions + project library)

- **Altera IP Catalog / megafunctions** ([megafunctions-ip-cores.md](../../docs/standards/megafunctions-ip-cores.md)): when FIFO/RAM/DSP/PLL or inferred-template logic applies and the user did **not** already name the IP — **ask** **IP Catalog megafunction** vs **custom RTL**. Do not add generated IP `.v` without `.ip`/`.qip` or pull from `/quartus/libraries/megafunctions`.
- **Project library** (`km_hssi_*`, [rtl-macro-library.md](../../docs/design/rtl-macro-library.md)): when a catalog macro matches and the user did **not** name it — **ask** **library macro** vs **custom/inline** logic.
- Do **not** silently pick either path without confirmation.

## Selective standards (do not read everything)

- Read [docs/standards/INDEX.md](../../docs/standards/INDEX.md) first; load **only** topic files that match user keywords.
- Read **only** the matched **section** of design source docs (see `docs/design/INDEX.md`), not full documents.
- Load [docs/examples/](../../docs/examples/) for matched topics; on fallback, use examples only if the user points to them or the task clearly matches (e.g. CDC → `examples/cdc/`).

## Output discipline

- Separate **facts** (standards, user, RTL in workspace) from **recommendations**.
- State which topic files and design sections were used.

## Invoke

- `@rtl-design` — primary
- `@rtl-coding-standards` — same router

## Scope

- Verilog and SystemVerilog RTL in open workspace unless user expands scope.
- Match project dialect; no SV-only constructs in `.v` without user approval.
